The paper discusses a new DRAM-based true random number generator (TRNG) and its methodology for extracting true random numbers from commodity DRAM devices. This involves violating DRAM access timing parameters to induce read errors that exhibit true random behavior. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer security (cs.CR), architecture (cs.AR), information theory (cs.IT), software engineering (cs.SE), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
